                    <span>The Amulet of Samarkand by Jonathon Stroud is one of the best and well-written books I have ever came by. It ties mystery and murder into fantasy in a dark tantalizing tale that will keep your nose buried in its pages for months. This book contains a young wizard, seeking revenge, a clever and ruthless master, and a djinni, a strange mystical creature living for thousands of years on end. I recomend this book to anyone who loves fantasy and adventure with just a quirky twist of mystery. A fantastic read.   </span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Great!!!</div>
